DEMANDABLE WEB (DW) DUAL-LICENSING POLICY

This repository is licensed under a dual-licensing structure to promote rapid industry 
adoption, open collaboration, and technical standardisation, while preserving commercial 
viability for proprietary integrations.

1. COMMUNITY EDITION (AGPL-3.0)
The core smart contracts, AI engine modules, and DApp clients in this repository are 
licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License version 3 (AGPL-3.0), as detailed 
below. Anyone is free to copy, modify, distribute, and run this software. However, 
if you modify the software and run it as a service over a network (e.g., hosting a 
competing home services DApp or contractor registry), you MUST make your modified 
source code publicly available under the AGPL-3.0.

2. ENTERPRISE COMMERCIAL LICENSE
If you are an enterprise aggregator, ERP provider, or contractor network that wishes 
to integrate, modify, or extend the core Demandable Web protocol without being subject 
to the copyleft requirements of the AGPL-3.0, you must obtain a commercial license 
from Demandable Web. Please contact licensing@demandableweb.com.

